sequenceDiagram

actor User
participant Browser
participant View as advanced_search view
participant Registry as SEARCH_REGISTRY
participant Fields as find_searchable_fields
participant Service as AdvancedSearchService
participant Filter as FilterBuilder
participant Manager as SearchableManager
participant DB as Database

%% =========================
%% STEP 1: LOAD MODELS
%% =========================

User->>Browser: Open advanced search
Browser->>View: GET /search/advanced

View->>Registry: get searchable models
Registry-->>View: model list

View-->>Browser: display models
Browser-->>User: user selects model

%% =========================
%% STEP 2: LOAD FIELDS
%% =========================

Browser->>View: select model
View->>Fields: find_searchable_fields(model)
Fields-->>View: list of fields

View-->>Browser: display filter form

%% =========================
%% STEP 3: EXECUTE SEARCH
%% =========================

User->>Browser: set filters + optional query
Browser->>View: GET /search/advanced?filters...

View->>Service: advanced_search(query, model, filters)

Service->>Filter: build_filters(model, filters)
Filter-->>Service: Django filter kwargs

Service->>Manager: filter(**kwargs)
Manager->>DB: apply filters
DB-->>Manager: filtered queryset

alt query_text provided
    Service->>Manager: search(query_text)
    Manager->>DB: full-text search
    DB-->>Manager: ranked results
end

Manager-->>Service: final queryset
Service-->>View: results

View-->>Browser: render results
Browser-->>User: display filtered + searched results